# SHA-256 pin for the phi-crypto C-ABI staticlib (libphi_crypto.a) — supply-chain integrity
# gate. The chain links this staticlib only under -tags phicrypto_cgo, and
# CI verifies the freshly built artifact against this pin before the cgo link.
#
# This hash is SINGLE-PLATFORM: it is valid ONLY for the exact canonical toolchain below. A build
# on any other OS, architecture, or Rust version (e.g. a local macOS build) will NOT match it.
#
# Canonical build environment (mirrors the .github/workflows/ci.yml `cgo-verifier` job):
#   * OS / target triple : Linux x86_64  ->  x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu
#   * Rust toolchain     : 1.96.0  (pinned via dtolnay/rust-toolchain in ci.yml; an exact version,
#                          not "stable", because a new Rust release would change this hash)
#   * source             : Port-PHI/phi-crypto at the revision that job checks out
#   * build command      : RUSTFLAGS="--remap-path-prefix=$(pwd)=." \
#                            cargo build --release --locked --offline
#       --locked              pinned Cargo.lock (no dependency drift)
#       --offline             vendored crates only (no network)
#       --remap-path-prefix   path-independent object files -> reproducible, path-stable staticlib
#
# Regenerate in that environment with `make phicrypto-lib && make phicrypto-lib-pin`, review the new
# value, then commit this file. Format: "<sha256>  libphi_crypto.a" (sha256sum -c compatible).
9b711073df29928922c393f04330a618dfbdefbd83e4c0182a866b548ba56ccd  libphi_crypto.a
